<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" ><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="3.10.0">Jekyll</generator><link href="http://localhost:4000/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="http://localhost:4000/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2025-09-03T10:41:53+02:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/feed.xml</id><title type="html">Paul Gondolf</title><subtitle>Mathematics PhD student at University of Tübingen. Interested in quantum information theory, mathematical physics, software development and machine learning.</subtitle><entry><title type="html">How to setup a similar page</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/post/2025-08-30-website-setup-guide/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="How to setup a similar page" /><published>2025-08-30T00:00:00+02:00</published><updated>2025-08-30T00:00:00+02:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/post/website-setup-guide</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/post/2025-08-30-website-setup-guide/"><![CDATA[<p>This guide explains how to set up and customize this Jekyll-based website template.</p>

<h2 id="quick-start">Quick Start</h2>

<h3 id="prerequisites">Prerequisites</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Ruby (2.7+)</li>
  <li>Bundler gem</li>
  <li>Git</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="installation">Installation</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Fork or clone this repository</li>
  <li>Navigate to the project directory</li>
  <li>
    <p>Install dependencies:</p>

    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>bundle <span class="nb">install</span>
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Start the development server:</p>

    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>bundle <span class="nb">exec </span>jekyll serve
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Visit <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">http://localhost:4000</code> to see your site</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="configuration">Configuration</h2>

<h3 id="site-settings-_configyml">Site Settings (_config.yml)</h3>

<p>Update the main configuration file with your information:</p>

<div class="language-yaml highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="na">title</span><span class="pi">:</span> <span class="s2">"</span><span class="s">Your</span><span class="nv"> </span><span class="s">Name"</span>
<span class="na">email</span><span class="pi">:</span> <span class="s">your.email@example.com</span>
<span class="na">description</span><span class="pi">:</span> <span class="pi">&gt;-</span>
  <span class="s">Your professional description here.</span>
<span class="na">url</span><span class="pi">:</span> <span class="s2">"</span><span class="s">https://yourusername.github.io"</span>
<span class="na">github_username</span><span class="pi">:</span> <span class="s">your-github-username</span>
<span class="na">orcid_id</span><span class="pi">:</span> <span class="s">0000-0000-0000-0000</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="page-templates--usage">Page Templates &amp; Usage</h2>

<h3 id="cv-page-cvmd">CV Page (cv.md)</h3>

<p>The CV template supports structured data for education, teaching, and work experience:</p>

<div class="language-yaml highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nn">---</span>
